Our stay at José's place started on the wrong foot as to our surprise when entering the apartment the washing machine was broken, the shutters of the bedroom window were stuck closed, the bedroom TV was missing and the WiFi was spotty. We contacted José immediately and he was very prompt responding. He had very good intentions trying to make up for the inconveniences, proposed to come and install a blackout the next morning and lend us keys to do laundry in another building. Unfortunately the next morning we waited for him between 9:30 and 10am as scheduled but at 10:15am we had no news. We contacted him and he said he had an inconvenience but could come around noon instead. Since we had already reorganized our day we decided to instead leave the window shutters as they were during our stay and drop off our laundry at a nearby place. Jose respected our decision and covered the cost of our laundry. At this point the WiFi was still spotty after 24h, he had the modem restarted (since it is located in the apartment next door) and after that the internet was functional for the remainder of our stay :) We must say the cleanliness of the apartment was spotless, the sheets on the bed and the cover looked new and the mattress and pillows were in pristine condition, the apartment was well equipped and very comfortable. The location is next to the river so walking by it is very convenient, easily accessible by public buses to go to other parts of town. Our stay would have been perfect if we hadn't had the issues upon arrival or we would have been informed of the non functional washing machine and window shutters in advance. Jose had great intentions in making our stay enjoyful and recommended many good restaurants, supermarkets and points of interest as a local.
